{
  "schema_version": "0.1.0",
  "_comment": "GlassWorm v2 campaign targeting VS Code / Cursor / Windsurf / VSCodium via Open VSX. 72 extensions identified by Socket.dev and Koi Security in March-April 2026, cloning popular extensions with invisible Unicode PUA-character payloads and Solana blockchain C2. Six confirmed malicious; remaining acted as sleeper packages. All entries use ecosystem 'editor-extension' and match the normalized <publisher>.<name> format emitted by the editorext scanner. Versions are set to '*' via a single-element array because the malicious publisher accounts are entirely attacker-controlled (no legitimate versions exist). Sources: Socket.dev (72 Open VSX extensions, March 2026), The Hacker News (73 fake extensions, April 2026), Aikido.dev (GlassWorm Zig dropper, April 2026). Additionally includes the Anivia Stealer/OctoRAT Prettier impersonation (publishingsofficial.prettier-vscode-plus, November 2025) and the fake Solidity extension used in the $500K Cursor crypto theft (July 2026).",
